result.execSummary:
The defendant Jaral R Mccollum was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jaral R Mccollum is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jaral R Mccollum was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Jaral R Mccollum was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Jaral R Mccollum was found guilty of Person Duty to Aid/Report Crime, a class C misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.34(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record.
